The project budget was $600 million. The Division of Security and Technology (DST) provides
Information Technology related services and support on behalf of the Office of Chief Financial Officer
(OCFO) of the Department of Labor (DOL). The DST's functional areas are information security; technology support; troubleshooting; infrastructure management; change management; incident management; systems analysis; application development; database administration; executive reporting; A- 123 Audit reviews; enterprise architecture; certification & accreditation; security; continuous monitoring, audit support and tracking; project management; program management, and quality assurance. The DST represents OCFO on various IT-related committees in/out of Department of Labor (DOL). Ensure staff
compliance with security protocols in accordance with DOL personnel and administrative policy HIPAA privacy and security and policies procedures manuals. The DST's staff is comprised of information security officers, database administrators, programmers, systems analysts, program management, and other information technology IT-related specialists necessary to the OCFO mission and operations. The
DST staff supports contractors to develop, implement, and coordinate activities designed to ensure, protect, and restore information technology (IT) infrastructure system services, as well as financial management systems and capabilities. The DST is responsible for executing the government's compliance oversight and control over OCFO systems relating to federal employees group health data, pension data and unemployment benefits to name a few to the US Congress, US Treasury and the DOL. The DST performs quality assurance activities to monitor and remediate technology and security processes within the OCFO. The Division is responsible for communicating enterprise architecture updates to DOL and as well as understanding and communicating architectural issues within OCFO financial systems. The DST provides infrastructure management service for OCFO servers, desktop, laptop, mobile and customer application support. The DST provides expert technical advice and analysis to the Office of the OCFO.
The DST provides information security and quality assurance duties for all OCFO IT systems and seeks to meet or exceed federally mandates of the Federal Information Security Management Act, Federal
Information System Control Audit, and Office Management and Budget, (OMB Circular A-123), A-130.
Additionally, the DST will provide weekly audit dashboards for OCFO across DOL tracking responsible party performance, as well as, develop and maintain monthly dashboard displaying performance metrics.
